10:This year, we re-evaluated the cost effectiveness of direct cash
11:transfers as implemented by our friends at GiveDirectly. Our complete
12-writeup is here, and full of fascinating details, but the main headline
13:is: we now estimate that GiveDirectly’s flagship cash program is 3 to 4
14:times more cost-effective than we’d previously estimated.
15-
16-It is important to note two things: (1) this won’t alter our Top
17-Charities list or our grantmaking—we believe that the programs we
18:currently direct funding to are at least twice as cost-effective as this
19:new estimate, so we don’t expect to support GiveDirectly’s flagship
20-program in the near term; and (2) this update is the result of
21:re-evaluating the evidence underpinning GiveDirectly’s program, which we
22:hadn’t formally done since 2019—the structure of GiveDirectly’s program
23-has not changed (though they are now carrying it out in more locations
24-since our last evaluation).
25-
26-We share more information about our research below. You can read our
27:full, detailed report here. You can read GiveDirectly’s blog post on our
28-re-evaluation here.
29-
30:Refresher: What is GiveDirectly’s flagship program?
31-
32:GiveDirectly’s Cash for Poverty Relief program sends one-time cash
33-transfers of approximately $1,000 via mobile money platforms to
34-households living in poor regions of Kenya, Malawi, Mozambique, Rwanda,
35-and Uganda. These transfers are unconditional: there are no strings
36-attached, and only very basic eligibility requirements.¹The basic
37-eligibility requirements are: (1) recipients must permanently reside in
38-the targeted village, (2) recipients must not have received a
39:GiveDirectly transfer previously, and (3) at least one member of the
40-household must be over 18.
41-
42-What is driving GiveWell’s updated estimate?
43-
44-There are four primary drivers contributing to increased
45:cost-effectiveness, the most impactful of which is the increased
46-consumption accruing to non-recipients (“spillovers”). The table below
47-shows (in order of importance) how much each driver impacted our
48:bottom-line estimates across the locations of GiveDirectly’s flagship
