145:At the best-guess defaults (100,000 draws), the portfolio produces a median of `{python} F["median"]` QALYs, with a 90% interval of `{python} F["p05"]` to `{python} F["p95"]` and a mean of `{python} F["mean"]`. The blended cost-effectiveness — dollars given over QALYs produced, at the median — is `{python} F["blended"]` per QALY. Monetized at the U.S. Department of Health and Human Services' value per QALY, the health alone repays the giving 4.9 times over (90% interval 2.1–11.0). @fig-dist shows the full distribution.
